description:
This app contains all 48 lessons from the book “Get Rid of your Accent for Beginners”, which is the latest book in the series “Get Rid of your Accent”. See our other accent reduction apps and books on www.batcsglobal.com.

This new app provides a total solution for accent reduction.

Content

You practice English pronunciation first in words, then in useful phrases, short sentences, amusing verses, rhythmic and articulation exercises and short passages. We selected the most essential vocabulary for those who begin to learn English.

Functionality

• The app plays audio tracks;
• Students can repeat, copy pronunciation, liaisons, and intonation;
• Students can record themselves;
• Students can hear their voice and compare their pronunciation with the model.


The app will help you sound confident and educated. You will:

• Master all English sounds of RP (Received Pronunciation). RP is the neutral accent of educated southern English and the chief accent taught to foreigners who wish to learn the British model. In the past it was also referred to as Oxford English, Queens English, or BBC English;
• Drill articulation exercises, consonant clusters and word endings to make your consonants clear and crisp;
• Learn patterns of English intonation and sentence stress;
• Master fluency, speaking in phrases, linking words together.


This is what people say about this new book:

"This is a book useful for both those starting on the path of accent reduction and those that have used any of the previous books by Olga and Linda (my case). The method is the same, but this volume concentrates on the most used words and expressions of daily life and I have found it really helpful in correcting my pronunciation of many commonly used phrases. I have also found the apps really helpful in comparing my pronunciation to the correct one, much more practical than the CDs." Alan Perez, Amazon customer

"Excellent book. As a teacher, I need to find a way to reduce my foreign accent, to deliver good lessons and clear information to my students. This book is a very recommended tool, you only need time to practise and repeat as much as you can the different activities." An Amazon customer
